Neural Networks, Knowledge-Based Systems. 

Neural Networks: The paper describes the use of neural networks to diagnose faults in local telephone loops and compares their performance to that of an expert system called MAX. The paper also discusses the use of neural network ensembles and their superior performance compared to standard neural networks.

Knowledge-Based Systems: The paper discusses the use of an expert system called MAX, which is a knowledge-based system, to aid human experts in diagnosing faults in local telephone loops. The paper also describes the use of knowledge-based neural networks, which incorporate expert knowledge into the neural network architecture, and their superior performance compared to standard neural networks.
